@rathoregee Font Awesome is essentially a web font, so it requires [@font-face support](http://caniuse.com/#feat=fontface).

If you have customers behind enterprise group policy which forbids font-face, unfortunately you can't use Font Awesome (as well as other webfonts).

You could go for .svg or .png sprites, please give a look at this project: https://github.com/encharm/Font-Awesome-SVG-PNG

